<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-366] Document NRS Delay</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-366</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;NRS Delay is a new feature slated for Lustre 2.10. It probably does not need extensive documentation because it is intended for use in development and testing, however we should probably at least document how it can be configured via the lctl command.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The commit comment for the patch contains a number of examples. Patch is here &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/14701&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/14701&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The development ticket is &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6283&quot; title=&quot;NRS Delay Policy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6283&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6283&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
